author: Veronica Dagher
title: MassMutual Commits $100 Million to Financial-Literacy Effort
text:
Massachusetts Mutual Life Insurance Co. has committed $100 million to its effort to boost the financial savvy of people in their 20s and 30s.
Last October, the insurer launched the Society of Grownups, an online financial-literacy initiative with currently one physical location where young adults can go to learn about topics such as saving for retirement and negotiating a salary.
